    <div class="fact-box">
        <h2> 💥 What Are the Main Types of Pollution?</h2>
        <dl>
            <dt> Air Pollution</dt>
            <dd> When harmful gases and smoke enter the air, it becomes hard to breathe.
                Cars, factories, and burning trash cause this.</dd>

            <dt>Water Pollution</dt>
            <dd> Plastic, oil, and chemicals dumped in rivers and
                oceans kill marine life and make water unsafe to drink.</dd>
            <dt> Plastic Pollution</dt>
            <dd> Single-use plastics like bottles and bags stay
                in the environment for hundreds of years. Animals often eat them and die..</dd>

        </dl>

        <img src="WhatsApp Image 2025-07-24 at 1.57.36 PM.jpeg" class="img" alt="air Pollution">
        <img src="w.jpeg" class="img" alt="water Pollution">
        <img src="p.jpeg" class="img" alt="plastic Pollution">
        <button class="btn"><a href="https://www.unep.org">Source</a></button>
    </div>

    <div class="fact-box">
        <h2> 🔥 What’s Causing Pollution — and What’s the Cost?</h2>
        <h2>Main Causes:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Factories releasing toxic gases</li>
            <li>Cars and buses burning fuel</li>
            <li>Throwing trash in nature</li>
            <li>Using too much plastic</li>
            <li>Cutting down forests</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Main Effects:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Global warming and climate change</li>
            <li>Sick animals and dying plants</li>
            <li>Dirty water and food</li>
            <li>Breathing problems in humans</li>
            <li>Extreme weather (heatwaves, floods)</li>
        </ul>

        <a href="https://climatekids.nasa.gov">Source</a>
    </div>
    <div class="fact-box">
        <h2>  🌟 Be Part of the Solution, Not the Pollution!</h2>
        <h2>Simple Actions You Can Take:</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Reduce, Reuse, Recycle ♻️</li>
            <li>Say no to plastic bags</li>
            <li>Walk or bike instead of using a car</li>
            <li>Plant trees and care for plants</li>
            <li>Join or start a clean-up team</li>
        </ol>

        <a href="https://www.who.int/health-topics/air-pollution">Source</a>
